# Your rule content

- Use canonical Alpine.js as much as possible
- Use Tailwindcss for all styling
- Keep logic simple, straightforward, and cleanly organized
- Reduce duplication where possible and remove unused code when possible
- Logically organize methods and functionality to be near each other in the file
- Always keep accessibility in mind
    - ensure proper contrast when choosing colors
    - always add aria- tags to describe the content in divs
    - add descriptive ids to divs
    - Use heading styles to designate content organization
    - Alternative text (alt text) is required for all visuals that provide meaningful information
    - Check that color is not the only visual means of distinguishing a visual element

